Export full SQL database configuration and Windows VM association to CSV
Data Engineering · SQL Infrastructure · Reporting
Description
As a database administrator / infrastructure engineer, I need a comprehensive export of every SQL database 
configuration and its associated Windows VM settings into a structured CSV format. This export must 
capture every configurable parameter — from instance-level settings and authentication modes to storage, network, memory, security policies, and Windows VM host details.
The goal is to provide a single, auditable, version-controllable snapshot of the entire SQL estate that can be used for compliance, capacity planning, migration scoping, and incident response.

A single CSV file (or one per category with a manifest) is generated covering all SQL instances and their associated Windows VM hosts
Every field listed in the scope above is present as a named column in the export — no fields omitted
Each row uniquely identifies a SQL database by instance name + database name + host VM, with no duplicate rows
All Windows VM host details are correctly associated to the SQL instance running on that VM
NULL or unavailable fields are represented as empty cells, not errors, so the CSV remains parseable
Export script/process is documented with instructions to re-run on demand
Output validated against at least 2 known SQL instances to confirm accuracy of values
CSV is UTF-8 encoded with headers on row 1 and passes import test into Excel and Power BI without errors
Sensitive fields (passwords, service account credentials) are masked or excluded from the export
Reviewed and signed off by the DBA lead before closing the ticket
